data.title: Public key encryption - AP CSP (practice)

data.text:
The sending computer sends more data than the receiving computer receives; some data is lost in translation.

The start of the data is encrypted with a different key than the end of the data.

The sender and receiver do not use the same key for encrypting and decrypting the data.
